<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="1277" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="22.[178,1085,1149,1259]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1277">
The species was hitherto known from East Siberia, Russian Far East, 
<collectingCountry box="[912,972,1150,1171]" name="Japan" pageId="22" pageNumber="1277">Japan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[986,1085,1149,1171]" name="Mongolia" pageId="22" pageNumber="1277">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
and the Chinese provinces of Heilongjiang and Nei Mongol (
<bibRefCitation author="JAEGER B" box="[806,997,1179,1200]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1277" pagination="913 - 962" refId="ref36075" refString="JAEGER B. (1993): Revision der ostasiatischen Arten des Bradycellus- Subgenus Tachycellus MORAWITZ: 1. Teil: Die anchomenoides-Gruppe (Col., Carabidae). - Linzer biologische Beitrage 25 (2): 913 - 962." type="journal article" year="1993">JAEGER 1993: 947</bibRefCitation>
, JAEGER &amp; WRASE 1994: 481, 
<bibRefCitation author="JAEGER B" box="[404,714,1208,1230]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1277" pagination="397 - 406" refId="ref36783" refString="JAEGER B. &amp; B. M. KATAEV (2003): Carabidae: Harpalini: Subtribe Stenolophina. Pp. 397 - 406. - In: LOBL I. &amp; A. SMETANA (eds), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera, Vol. 1. Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga. Stenstrup: Apollo Books, 819 pp." type="book chapter" year="2003">JAEGER &amp; KATAEV 2003: 401</bibRefCitation>
). It is here also recorded for Beijing and Gansu for the first time.
</paragraph>
